    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A paint made by grinding pigments with a drying oil such as linseed oil. After 1940 alkyd binders were often added to oil paint to provide faster drying times.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
